\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Bladimir lossky - no theology without mysticism.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Theosis - becoming diving - eastern othrodox church. Hesychat- apophatic - god is beyond human understanding. Clement of alexandria - we can only attain to god in study of what he is not. Pseudo-dionysius - the mystical theology. We can never know god or what he is because he is unknowable. It is through unknowing that we approach the ineffable darkness of the godhead.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Western mystics like eckhart}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Him who is above every possible object of knowledge. Proceeding by negations one ascens from the inferior degrees of being to the highest, by progressily setting aside all that can be known, in order to draw near to the Unknown in the darkness of absolute ignorance.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Me - He is that which is Unknown. He resides in the darkness of absoulute ignorance, and so to find him, one must set aside all that can be known.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 A means of attaining union with him through prayer - abandoning knowledge - meditation.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Hesychasm - tradition of meditation and prayer in the eastern orthodox church. 14th century and before. Unity with god. Direct experience with gods light through turning inward of contemplation. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Hesychia - inner stillness. Body postures and breathing techniques and prayers. Head bowed, chin reaching chest, eyes on the heart, breathing done in time with the prayers. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 THe Jesus prayer - Lord Jesus Christ, Son of God, Have mercy upon me. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Not dissimilar to yoga. But body postures are to simply aid concentration.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Turn inward, journy into apophatic darkness, beyond all understanding and paradoxically, the light of god is experienced.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Each of us is a \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91living theology\u8217\'92, and because we are god\u8217\'92s icon, we can find god by looking within our own heart, by \u8216\'91returning within ourselves\u8217\'92.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The kingdom of God is within you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93He who knows himself, knows God.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93When you see your brother or sister, you see god.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93God became human so that we might become God.\u8221\'94 - athanasius.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Barlaam of seminara}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Controversy - called it heretical - how could god\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s light be experienced with the eyes. This must be a created light, not the creator itself.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Gregory palamas - mt. Athos. So successful that he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s mainstream}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Triads for the defence of those who practice sacred quietude.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s essence and God\u8217\'92s energies}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Essence of god - totally beyond all comprehension . God is not a nature, for he is above all nature. He is not a being, for he is above all beings, no single thing of all that is created has or ever will have even the slightest communion with the supreme nature or nearness to it.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Energies - }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Relationship of god with the created world  - how god manifests himself to created things}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 - not created - fully god but not the same as the essence.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 They are outpourings of the divine nature which cannot set bouds to itself, for god is more tha nessence. The energies might be described as that mode of existence of the trinity which is outside of its inaccessible essence. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 All of creation is a gigantic Burning Bush, permeated but not consumed by the ineffable and wondrous fire of God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s energies.}
