\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Marguerite porete}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Passed by god in the abyss. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 I speak in all truth, that this same ligh (the spark of the soul) is not content with the simple divine essence in its repose, as it neither gives nor receives; but it wants to know the source of this issence, it wants to go into the simple ground, into the quiet desert ,into which distinction never gazed, not the father ,nor the son, nor the holy spirit. In breaking through, when I come to be free of will of myself and of god\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s will and of all his works and of god himself, then I am above all created things, and I am neither god nor creature, but I am what I was and what I shall remain, now and eternally. As long as the soul has god, knows god and is aware of god, she is far from god. The greatest honor the soul can pay to god is to leave god to himself and be free of him. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 When complete self-realization has been reached, and we have returned to the limitless ground where the soul and god is without distinction, god unbecomes or dies, we leave god behind and exist only in the ground which is god\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s true essence. We have broken through into total unity with the divine.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You should completly sink away for your you-ness and flow into his his-ness and your you and his his shall become one \u8216\'91our\u8217\'92 so totally that with him you eternally comprehend his unbecoming isness and his unnamed nothingness.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Once you break through into the ground of god\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s being, we let go of all virtues and religious obligations}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mahmud shabistari}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 When absolute existence is alluded to, people use the word \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8221\'94 as a matter of expression. When reality has taken form through individuation, you refer to It in language with the word \u8220\'93I\u8221\'94. You and I are \u8216\'91accidents\u8217\'92 of the Essence of Being, like openings in the covering of the lamp of Being.}
